HEADWORD: Dakotas
<hw>Da*ko"tas</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl</pos>.; <sing>sing.
<singw>Dacota</singw> <pr>(<?/)</pr></sing>. <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld>
<def>An extensive race or stock of Indians, including many tribes,
mostly dwelling west of the Mississippi River; -- also, in part, called
<altname>Sioux</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>Dacotahs</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
